						<p>Prince of Wales Museum, Slab No. B. B. 350.</p>						

						<p>8th-9th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record of about the 8th-9th century A.D. gives a number of epithets such as Kuḷaniti, Kaḍugati-sēbya, Sarbba-satyaniratar, <hi rend="italic">etc.,</hi> of Kōmaḷiga. States that the memorial stone was made by the stone-cutter Kanne.</p>						

